  "summary": "Capesize\nThe Capesize market experienced a steady decline this week, with the BCI 5TC falling from $24,521 on Monday to $21,676 by Friday. The Atlantic saw significant fixing activity, particularly from South Brazil to China, but an oversupply of tonnage in ballast and weakening demand led to a softening trend. The C3 index dropped from $25.97 on Monday to $24.69 by Friday.",
